As Duane wrote to Dr. Math
On 08/24/2004 at 11:09:22 (Eastern Time),
>[Question]
>Can x^4 + 16 be factored?
>
>[Difficulty]
>Factoring the sum of two fourth powers (or squares)
>
>[Thoughts]
>I know x^2 + 16 can not be factored without going to complex 
>numbers.  But our teacher says this can be factored into to quadratic 
>polynomials without using i.

Hello Duane,

Surprisingly, it can be factored:

(x^4+a^4) = (x^2 + Sqrt[2]a*x + a^2)(x^2 - Sqrt[2]a*x + a^2)

